FBIS4-59022 "drnes090_n_94002" FBIS-NES-94-090 Daily Report 10 May 1994 LEBANON Refuses Visitors 10 May Refuses Visitors 10 May NC1005054394 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0430 GMT 10 May 94 NC1005054394 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] In a statement issued at dawn today, the Cabinet's General Secretariat says that Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri thanks all the Lebanese citizens who flocked to his residence yesterday. The statement notes that the prime minister apologizes for not receiving other citizens and popular delegations today. The statement stresses that contacts are continuing to resolve the political situation in the country.
